---
import Layout from "./layouts/base.astro";

const title = "docupix";
---

<Layout title={title}>
    <div
        class="is-flex is-justify-content-start is-align-items-center is-flex-direction-column mt-6"
        id="app"
    >
        <h1
            class="is-size-3 has-text-weight-bold is-capitalized has-text-centered"
        >
            CONVERT YOUR PDF DOCUMENT TO PNG IMAGES
        </h1>

        <div
            class="box dropzone-container is-flex is-justify-content-start is-align-items-center is-flex-direction-column is-flex-wrap-wrap"
        >
            <div
                class="box dropzone is-flex is-justify-content-center is-align-items-center is-flex-direction-column mt-6"
            >
                <i class="bx bx-folder-plus is-size-1"></i>
                <p>Drop Image Here</p>
                <input
                    type="file"
                    name=""
                    id="input"
                    accept="application/pdf"
                    hidden
                />
                <button class="button mt-3" id="inputBtn">Select Files</button>
            </div>
            <div
                class="box file-attached is-flex is-justify-content-space-between"
                id="filezone"
            >
                <div class="is-flex">
                    <i class="bx bx-paperclip is-size-4 mr-4"></i>
                    <p id="filename"></p>
                </div>
                <div class="is-flex">
                    <p id="filesize">0.1MB</p>
                    <button class="" id="processBtn"
                        ><i class="bx bx-save is-size-4 ml-3" id="send"
                        ></i></button
                    >
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="box box-danger hidden" id="boxDanger">
                <p class="has-text-centered">FILE MUST BE PDF FORMAT</p>
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="box loading-container hidden" id="loadingContainer">
            <div class="loader"></div>
            <p id="loadingText">Converting...</p>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div class="is-flex is-align-items-center is-flex-direction-column">
        <div class="box content" id="content">
            <h2 class="title is-4">Convert PDF to PNG</h2>

            <p>
                DocuPix is a simple, free tool that lets you convert PDF files
                into high-quality PNG images directly in your browser. Unlike
                traditional converters, everything happens on your device, no
                uploads, no waiting, no risk.
            </p>

            <p>
                PDF files are great for documents because they look consistent
                across devices. However, they are not always supported
                everywhere, especially on platforms that prefer images. PNG, on
                the other hand, is widely supported across web, mobile, and
                apps, making it easier to share and use.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="title is-5">Why convert PDF to PNG?</h3>
            <p>
                Converting PDF to PNG allows you to turn document pages into
                images that are easier to upload, share, and preview. For
                example, you can quickly post a page from a PDF to social media,
                include it in presentations, or use it in design projects.
            </p>

            <p>
                PNG format also preserves visual quality without compression
                artifacts, making it ideal for text-heavy documents,
                screenshots, and graphics.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="title is-5">How does DocuPix work?</h3>
            <p>Using DocuPix is straightforward:</p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    Select or drag and drop your PDF file into the converter
                </li>
                <li>DocuPix processes the file instantly in your browser</li>
                <li>Download the result as PNG images</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                If your PDF has multiple pages, each page will be converted into
                a separate PNG. You can download them individually or as a
                single ZIP file for convenience.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="title is-5">Fast, free, and private</h3>
            <p>
                DocuPix is designed with privacy in mind. Your files never leave
                your device, there is no upload to any server. This means your
                data stays completely under your control.
            </p>

            <p>
                Since everything runs locally, the conversion process is also
                faster and works even with slow or unstable internet
                connections.
            </p>

            <hr>

            <h3 class="title is-5">Is it safe?</h3>
            <p>
                Yes. Because DocuPix runs entirely in your browser, your files
                are never stored, tracked, or processed remotely. There are no
                hidden uploads or background transfers — what you open stays on
                your device.
            </p>

            <p>Simple, secure, and efficient, that’s the DocuPix way.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script type="module" src="/src/scripts/pdfToPng.ts"></script>
</Layout>
